    "page_number": "119",
    "rule_number": "S.3.1",
    "definition": "Cost Event Objective\nThe Cost and Manufacturing Event evaluates the ability of the team to consider budget and\nincorporate production considerations for production and efficiency.\nMaking tradeoff decisions between content and cost based on the performance of each part\nand assembly and accounting for each part and process to meet a budget is part of Project\nManagement."
  },
  "S.3.2": {
    "page_number": "119",
    "rule_number": "S.3.2",
    "definition": "Cost Event Supplement\na. Additional specific information on the Cost and Manufacturing Event, including\nexplanation and requirements, is provided in the Formula SAE Cost Event Supplement\ndocument.\nb. Use the Formula SAE Cost Event Supplement to properly complete the requirements of\nthe Cost and Manufacturing Event.\nc. The Formula SAE Cost Event Supplement is available on the FSAE Online website"
  },
  "S.3.3": {
    "page_number": "119",
    "rule_number": "S.3.3",
    "definition": "Cost Event Areas"
  },
  "S.3.3.1": {
    "page_number": "119",
    "rule_number": "S.3.3.1",
    "definition": "Cost Report\nPreparation and submission of a report (the “Cost Report”)"
  },
  "S.3.3.2": {
    "page_number": "119",
    "rule_number": "S.3.3.2",
    "definition": "Event Day Discussion\nDiscussion at the Competition with the Cost Judges around the team’s vehicle."
  }
}

